Grace Mugabe, the First Lady of Zimbabwe and current secretary of the Zanu-PF women&#8217;s league, has told the Zanu-PF party women&#8217;s league that she is already the president, claiming to already plan and do everything with President Robert Mugabe.Zanu-PF is reportedly riddled with warring factions, as the leaders in the party get ready to compete over who will succeed Mugabe.Among the possible names are Grace Mugabe and the two vice presidents Phelekezela Mphoko and Emmerson Mnangagwa.Source: News24